<title>UK: Eurodis appoints new chief operating officer.</title>
<headline>Eurodis appoints new chief operating officer.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>British electronic components and systems supplier Eurodis Electron Plc said on Thursday it had appointed Edward Burgess as a director and chief operating officer.</p>
<p>Burgess, who takes up his job from May 12, is likely to take over as group chief executive in early 1998 to replace Barry Charles who will retire then.</p>
<p>Charles would then be a part-time vice chairman of the company, Eurodis said.</p>
